# Direct dependency manifest, consumed by `uv pip compile` to produce
# `requirements.lock.txt` (CUDA) and `requirements.cpu.lock.txt` (CPU).
#
# Phase A rigor-restoration note:
#   The original `requirements.txt` used unpinned `>=` constraints, which
#   prevents reproducibility across Colab / local environments. This file is
#   the canonical direct-dependency source; the two lock files derived from
#   it pin transitive deps exactly.
#
# Regenerate with:
#   uv pip compile requirements.in          -o requirements.lock.txt
#   uv pip compile --python-platform linux --python-version 3.11 \
#                  --extra-index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu \
#                  requirements.in          -o requirements.cpu.lock.txt
#
# Bump deps by editing this file, re-running the two commands above, and
# committing all three.

